transcript.text: Hello and welcome back to the Store Management tutorial series.

We have kept an open room for the store admin as well as the site admin to personalize the store web pages based on their actions, indent and other parameters, thus providing them with a tailored user experience.
For store personalization, we have given four different options to modify the content of the store, namely website logos, theme configuration, personalization pages, and custom CSS.
So let's get started.
To do the store branding or personalization, log into your admin panel and go to the store's listing page.
Select the store, then click on the Actions drop down and select the configuration option.
As mentioned earlier, you will have the widgets to manage the website logo, theme page, personalization, and custom CSS.
Let's begin with adding the website logos.
Here you can upload the logos for the website, mobile view, favicon, e-mail, designer, studio and Studio app and then save them.
Next, we have the option to personalize the website theme using the theme configuration widget.
Select if you want to apply any standard theme or want to have a custom theme.

On the selection of custom, you will have more options to select the theme and choose any specific color and on the basis of color, it will show you the options for primary and secondary colors which you can change as per your preference.
Once you have customized the theme, it will reflect on the front side of your store.
You can clearly view the change in the page body color and primary and secondary colors at the storefront.
Talking about our next personalization feature, it is Pages personalization for personalization of the login, registration and reset password pages.
The admin can add custom text, change the background color, add an image or a flash video in the background, and more.
You can personalize your login page, registration page, and password reset page using the variables shared in the help section.
Last but not the least, you can also personalize the custom CSS code as per your business requirement for more changes in your storefront.
This was all about how you can perform the private store branding or personalization.
If you have any questions, our support executives are here to help.
Just reach out through live chat on on printshop.com.
Thanks for tuning in.
